"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here with Scotty's Fermented Foods. I get asked all the time, what is living soil? How can you tell if your soil is living? And the easiest way to show this is to find an aggregate to point out the difference between living and dead. Here's a good one. So in this, you can see it's a bunch of random particles and they're all bound together. When you crush it, it should just break apart. And what's holding that together are what call what's called aggregates. And this is basically microbe poop, uh the mucus inside earthworms and all the living elements in your soil. That's biological glue. When you have uh that loose type of uh substance binding everything together, the aggregates, that's how you tell living soil. Those are the indicators. And uh nothing beats a good ass set of aggregates that holds so much more moisture and so much more carbon than uh just regular soil.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here with Scotty's Fermented Foods.\",\n      \"start\": 0.0,\n      \"end\": 2.16,\n      \"duration\": 2.16,\n      \"confidence\": 0.99,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.0,\n          \"end\": 0.08,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.967\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.08,\n          \"end\": 0.08,\n          \"duration\": 0.0,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.16,\n          \"end\": 0.24,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.24,\n          \"duration\": 0.0,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ody\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        }